HEADWORD: Enfreeze
<hw>En*freeze"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To freeze; to
congeal.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou hast <qex>enfrozened</qex> her disdainful breast.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

